Rating: 4
This dish was excellent-my whole family loved it, including my kids. The sauce was outstanding! I did what the cook from Aptos, CA did - I de-boned pork loin chops and used the bones in place of the riblets. I would use 6 chops the next time; 4 was not enough. I served it the Baked Apple Compote and Sweet Potato Puree with Brown Sugar and Sherry.

Rating: 3
A nice rendition of sauce poivrade without the hassle of making a demi-glace. I de-boned the pork loin chops and used them in place of the riblets. Didn't have currant jelly so I used leftover cranberry sauce flavored with candied ginger. No red wine vinegar left in my pantry so I substituted 1 T. each of balsamic, and white wine vinegar. Even with the improvising the sauce was delicious. Can't wait to make it again according to the recipe. I also seared the pork chops on the stovetop and finished in the oven. They were tender and juicy. Might possibly make the sauce to accompany a pork tenderloin for Christmas.

Rating: 4
