Rating: 3
The sauce is great! Plus it is very flexible. I've used it with steak by adding a bulb of roasted garlic as the last step.

Rating: 3
Sauce was absolutely delicious. Didn't quite know what riblets where so I used pork ribs as substitute. Also, didn't have currant jelly and used apricot and hoisin sauce as sub. The sauce definitely was something I would use again on other dishes. Served with braised red cabbage, apple compote, and whipped parsnips. Parsnips were so sweet (used low fat milk and half and half instead of cream). All that was needed was seasoning - sweet! Oven roasted pork chops after a quick sear on the stove. Delightful way to start the week!